                    <comment id="12755990" author="mduerig" created="Wed, 16 Sep 2009 13:19:25 +0100"  >This patch implements a proof of concept fix for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- implements javax.jcr.RepositoryFactory&lt;br/&gt;
- configuration is passed as map instead of URLs since (1): jsr 283 compliant and (2): parts of the configuration settings need to go to jcr2spi and parts need to be passed on to spi. This is kind of troublesome using URLs. The URL scheme can still be implemented on top of this for the more common use cases though. &lt;br/&gt;
- With this patch jcr2spi could be cleanly OSGi bundled by only exporting org.apache.jackrabbit.jcr2spi.factory (partial fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1991&quot; title=&quot;Create osgi bundles for all jars&quot;&gt;JCR-1991&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
- With this patch jackrabbit-jcr-client could be redesigned on top of Jcr2spiRepositoryFactory which would remove the compile time dependencies of jcr-client to the various spi implementations (improvement to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2041&quot; title=&quot;Create Jcr-Client Module&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-2041&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
